snippet.textDisplay:
Tyson was in great shape for the first fight. He went 12 rounds and got knocked down twice and still finished strong - that was being in shape.

He lost the fight from being careless in the last round, that's all.

Ben Davison did his job beautifully and was not to blame. Tyson won but got robbed and everyone with a half a brain knows that.

I understand you need to change things if they are not working but they were working, HE WON THE FIGHT!

Are you telling me that Ben Davison does not know how to throw power shots and take a man out - like Sugar-Hill. I think he does!

I fully get Ben Davison, he's the trainer. The trainer knows your strengths and weaknesses and it should be really the trainer that calls the shots, unfortunately it does not work like that when you have such a huge personality and mega-diva-star like Tyson Fury.

Remember who helped you through your hard times Tyson?

It is not nice to be undermined especially when you are a good trainer and done nothing wrong. If you lose and keep losing then change is a must and I get it. Also to improve you do need other people in to help, I do think a rash decision was made too quickly by Tyson, in the aftermath of the disappointment of his draw. Plus he was influenced by other people!

I'm sure Ben could see the small adjustments that needed to be made for TF V Dw 2

I personally think Tyson Fury should do the same again and box his head off but maul him a lot more, which hopefully will tire him out. When the time is right then try and take him out.

I do hope Tyson gets the win. - It could be an early night for Tyson if he decides to play fire with fire. OR is it all talk...

Good luck to both boxers and may the best man win!
